# Import Path Standards

Always use absolute imports with `@` alias instead of relative paths (`./` or `../`).

## Rules

### ✅ GOOD - Use @ alias
```typescript
import { Button } from "@repo/ui/button";
import { useGetAllProjects } from "@/modules/projects/app/hooks/use-get-all-projects";
import { ProjectListError } from "@/view/layouts/app/sidebar/components/project-list-error";
```

### ❌ BAD - Don't use relative paths
```typescript
import { Button } from "../../../../packages/ui/src/components/button";
import { useGetAllProjects } from "../../../modules/projects/app/hooks/use-get-all-projects";
import { ProjectListError } from "./components/project-list-error";
```

## Available Aliases (SPA App)

- `@/pages/*` - Points to `src/view/pages/*`
- `@/layouts/*` - Points to `src/view/layouts/*`
- `@/components/*` - Points to `src/view/components/*`
- `@/ui/*` - Points to `src/view/ui/*`
- `@/utils/*` - Points to `src/app/utils/*`
- `@/services/*` - Points to `src/app/services/*`
- `@/hooks/*` - Points to `src/app/hooks/*`
- `@/contexts/*` - Points to `src/app/contexts/*`
- `@/storage/*` - Points to `src/app/storage/*`
- `@/config/*` - Points to `src/app/config/*`
- `@/libs/*` - Points to `src/app/libs/*`
- `@/entities/*` - Points to `src/app/entities/*`
- `@/modules/*` - Points to `src/modules/*`

## Shared Packages

- `@repo/ui` - Shared UI components package
- `@repo/typescript-config` - Shared TypeScript configs
- `@repo/logger` - Shared logger package

## Why This Matters

- **Maintainability**: Easier to move files without breaking imports
- **Readability**: Clear where imports are coming from
- **Consistency**: Same pattern across the entire codebase
- **Refactoring**: IDEs can better track and update imports

## Migration Guide

When you see a relative import:
1. Identify the full path from `src/`
2. Replace with `@/` + the path from src
3. For shared packages, use the appropriate `@repo/*` alias
